sp_scores.title: Exploit Flame Eater's weakness to ice attacks.

tip_battle.message: Flame Eater is vulnerable to ice, kupo! Just watch out for the balloons and grenades it summons with Bomblet--when they Self-Destruct, it really hurts!
tip_battle.title: Flame Eater

dungeons.epilogue: In search of the espers, the Returners consulted with the monster expert Strago in the remote village of Thamasa, only to be given the cold shoulder. While the party spent the night in the village, a blaze engulfed Strago's house, with a young village girl named Relm trapped inside. As thanks for extinguishing the Flame Eater responsible, Strago agreed to guide them to the Esper Caves.
dungeons.name: Thamasa
dungeons.prologue: Terra's magic opens the Sealed Gate to the Esper World, and the espers spill out, driving away the Imperial forces. Fearing the espers, the Empire sues for peace, and asks for the Returners' help in tracking down the scattered espers before they cause more damage.

sp_scores.title: Defeat the Guard Leader before he uses Charge.

tip_battle.message: The Guard Leader appears with 2 Silver Lobos at his side. Focus your attacks on one target to thin their numbers. Use target to your advantage!
tip_battle.title: Guard Leader

dungeons.epilogue: The treasure hunter Locke rushes into the mines to save Terra, whom he finds unconscious. Imperial guards attack, and Locke is only able to escape with Terra thanks to the aid of a band of moogles. Safe for the time being, Locke takes Terra to Figaro Castle to meet with Edgar, a fellow Returner.
dungeons.name: Abandoned Mineshaft
dungeons.prologue: Freed from the Empire's hold on her mind, Terra flees Imperial guards and seeks refuge in the mines.

sp_scores.title: Defeat Ymir without triggering its counterattack.

tip_battle.message: Never, ever, EVER attack Ymir's shell, kupo, unless you want it to counterattack with Megavolt! Stay away from attacks and abilities that hit all targets so you don't hit the shell by accident!
tip_battle.title: Ymir

dungeons.epilogue: To an empire bent on dominating its rivals with newly-revived magic, news of a frozen esper in the mines to the north cannot be ignored. A resistance group from Narshe uses monsters to counter to the Imperial forces and protect the esper, but they are no match for the Empire's Magitek. Yet, before they can take the esper, its power envelops Terra...
dungeons.name: North Mines
dungeons.prologue: In a world where magic faded long ago, the Empire has found a girl born with magical abilities. Her encounter with an icebound esper sets in motion a chain of events that will change everything.

sp_scores.title: Exploit Orthros's weakness to fire attacks.

tip_battle.message: Orthros moves around the opera house like he owns the place, kupo! His actions change depending on where he is, but not his vulnerabilities. Fire and lightning will work throughout the battle!
tip_battle.title: Orthros

dungeons.epilogue: Setzer left a letter revealing his intention to kidnap the opera singer Maria during a performance, so Locke devised a plot to use Celes, a dead ringer for Maria, as bait to lure him out. Orthros appeared once more in an attempt to ruin their plans, to no avail. The group made contact with Setzer, and after much persuasion he offered his assistance.
dungeons.name: Opera House
dungeons.prologue: The party heads to the Opera House in order to make contact with Setzer, who owns an airship that can get them across the sea to the Empire.

sp_scores.title: Exploit the Tunnel Armor's weakness to lightning attacks.
Exploit the Tunnel Armor's weakness to water attacks.

tip_battle.message: Tunnel Armor may look like a mechanical brute, but watch out, kupo, lest its magic catches you unawares! Have Magic Break and Shell at the ready, and exploit its weaknesses to lightning and water!
tip_battle.title: Tunnel Armor

dungeons.epilogue: The Magitek Knight Celes has become disenchanted with the very Empire that created her. She turns traitor and is imprisoned until Locke comes to her rescue. With the help of Celes's Runic ability they are able to fight off the Imperial Magitek war machine "Tunnel Armor" and make their way to join the others in the Narshe Mines.
dungeons.name: South Figaro Cave
dungeons.prologue: Locke has come to South Figaro to disrupt the Empire's occupation. Trapped under watchful Imperial eyes, he finds an unlikely ally in Celes, an Imperial general. Together they escape through the cave beneath the town.

sp_scores.title: Exploit Humbaba's weakness to poison attacks.

tip_battle.message: Can you guess how much damage Humbaba's 1000 Needles attack does? A thousand, kupo! It's not a trick question. He's vulnerable to poison damage, so bring spells like Bio to this fight!
tip_battle.title: Humbaba

dungeons.epilogue: In Tzen, Celes rushed to aid Sabin as he held up a collapsing building to save a child trapped inside. Reunited once more, the allies vowed to gather their lost friends and end Kefka's reign of terror. Together they traveled to Mobliz, only to find Terra in a losing battle against Humbaba, a demon who had set his sights on the orphaned children Terra had been caring for.
dungeons.name: Mobliz
dungeons.prologue: Celes washes ashore near Albrook and learns from the townsfolk that Sabin is in Tzen, and Terra is in Mobliz.

sp_scores.title: Exploit Deathgaze's weakness to fire attacks.
Exploit Deathgaze's weakness to holy attacks.

tip_battle.message: Deathgaze uses Death to KO characters one by one, so bring Revive and Raise to get everyone back on their feet! It's vulnerable to fire and holy attacks, so hit hard and fast with those!
tip_battle.title: Deathgaze

dungeons.epilogue: Setzer and his friends had taken to the skies aboard the late Darill's airship, the Falcon. Yet no sooner did they start on their journey than they were attacked by Deathgaze. Chasing down the fleeing monster, they vanquished it, and once again set out across the skies.
dungeons.name: Falcon
dungeons.prologue: Setzer puts his grief behind him as he boards the restored Falcon and sets off on a journey with his old friends to see the ruined world.

sp_scores.title: Defeat Kefka without being KO'd.

tip_battle.message: Kefka attacks with magic, kupo! But he's immune to Silence, so you'll just have to heal through it! Make sure you have characters with healing abilities!
tip_battle.title: Kefka

dungeons.epilogue: With their combined strength, the resistance was able to repel Kefka's army and lead Terra back to the icebound esper, where a reaction occurred between her and the creature. Terra transformed into a being more esper than human and shot off into the sky. Her friends headed west in hopes of locating her.
dungeons.name: Esper Valley
dungeons.prologue: The scattered allies regroup in Narshe just as an Imperial force led by Kefka attempts to seize the esper. It falls to Terra and her allies to defend the town.

sp_scores.title: Defeat Ultima Weapon without being KO'd.

tip_battle.message: Ultima Weapon packs powerful magic attacks, kupo, and it doesn't have any special vulnerabilities. Weaken it with abilities like Armor Break, Power Break, and Magic Break!
tip_battle.title: Ultima Weapon

dungeons.epilogue: Forging their way past Ultima Weapon, the Returners reached the center of the Floating Continent where they found the statues of the Warring Triad. Gestahl turned their power against the party, temporarily paralyzing all but Celes. Kefka then offered to overlook her betrayal if she would kill her companions, but she refused and attacked. Wounded, Kefka flew into a rage and broke the seal on the Warring Triad, killing Gestahl when he tried to intervene.
dungeons.name: Floating Continent 1
dungeons.prologue: The party now makes for the center of the Floating Continent in order to keep Gestahl and Kefka from claiming the statues of the Warring Triad, said to contain the power to destroy the world.

sp_scores.title: Defeat Ymir without triggering its counterattack.

tip_battle.message: Never, ever, EVER attack Ymir's shell, kupo, unless you want it to counterattack with Megavolt! Stay away from attacks and abilities that hit all targets so you don't hit the shell by accident!
tip_battle.title: Ymir

dungeons.epilogue: To an empire bent on dominating its rivals with newly-revived magic, news of a frozen esper in the mines to the north cannot be ignored. A resistance group from Narshe uses monsters to counter the Imperial forces and protect the esper, but they are no match for the Empire's Magitek. Yet, before they can take the esper, its power envelops Terra...
dungeons.name: North Mines
dungeons.prologue: In a world where magic faded long ago, the Empire has found a girl born with magical abilities. Her encounter with an icebound esper sets in motion a chain of events that will change everything.

sp_scores.title: Exploit Dadaluma's weakness to poison attacks.

tip_battle.message: Dadaluma uses powerful abilities and potions to stay healed, but he's vulnerable to poison elemental damage, so spells like Bio come highly recommended, kupo! For some reason the Poison ability won't work on him, so don't use it, kupo!
tip_battle.title: Dadaluma

dungeons.epilogue: The party continued their search for Terra, despite difficulties in Zozo and run-ins with street thugs. After administering a beating to the head hoodlum, Dadaluma, they discovered Terra unconscious, but alive. The esper Ramuh, who was caring for Terra, informed the group that the espers held by the Empire may be able to awaken her. Transforming himself into Magicite, he entrusted his power to the Returners.
dungeons.name: Zozo
dungeons.prologue: Following word that Terra has been seen, the party goes from village to village looking for her. They eventually reach the town of Zozo, an impoverished hotbed of scum and villainy.

sp_scores.title: Exploit Tentacle (Bottom-Right)'s weakness to ice attacks.
Exploit Tentacle (Bottom-Left)'s weakness to fire attacks.

tip_battle.message: Each of the four Tentacles has a different vulnerability, kupo. Use the right element on the right tentacle, or you'll end up healing them!
tip_battle.title: Tentacles

dungeons.epilogue: Celes and Sabin followed Gerad into Figaro Castle, which had lost its ability to move through the desert sands. When they reached the engine room, they discovered why: a bizarre tentacle-like creature had wrapped itself around the castle's engine. Edgar finally abandoned his somewhat unconvincing guise as Gerad in the ensuing battle, and with the creature defeated, the castle was able to surface at last.
dungeons.name: Figaro Castle 2
dungeons.prologue: Celes' party leaves Terra in Mobliz and continues on to the port town of Nikeah, where they encounter a bandit named Gerad trying to enter Figaro Castle. The bandit looks suspiciously similar to Edgar...

sp_scores.title: Defeat Kefka without being KO'd.

tip_battle.message: Kefka attacks with magic, kupo! But he's immune to Silence, so you'll just have to heal through it! Make sure you have characters with healing abilities!
tip_battle.title: Kefka

dungeons.epilogue: With their combined strength, the resistance was able to repel Kefka's army and lead Terra back to the icebound esper, where a reaction occurred between her and the creature. Terra transformed into a being more esper than human and shot off into the sky. Her friends headed west in hopes of locating her.
dungeons.name: Esper Valley
dungeons.prologue: The scattered allies regroup in Narshe just as an Imperial force led by Kefka attempts to seize the esper. It falls to Terra and her allies to defend the town.

sp_scores.title: Exploit Crane (Lower)'s weakness to water attacks.
Exploit Crane (Upper)'s weakness to lightning attacks.

tip_battle.message: The Cranes are vulnerable to different elements, kupo, but there's one element that works on both of them: water! Attack with water and you can't go wrong!
tip_battle.title: Cranes

dungeons.epilogue: Locke's team fled the Magitek Research Facility, chased by Kefka's minions through the streets of Vector, until Setzer arrived on his airship, the Blackjack. Boarding the airship, they fought their way past Kefka's gigantic cranes and made the return journey to Zozo. There, they were able to use the magicite from Vector to revive Terra, who awakened with the knowledge that both human and esper blood flows in her veins.
dungeons.name: Vector
dungeons.prologue: Celes has teleported Kefka and herself away, but the power of her spell started a chain-reaction in the Magitek Factory. The party flees back into Vector with Kefka's minions in pursuit.

sp_scores.title: Exploit the Phantom Train's weakness to fire attacks.
Exploit the Phantom Train's weakness to lightning attacks.

tip_battle.message: The Phantom Train has a lot of abilities that hit the whole party, so keep an eye on everyone's health! And it may look like a machine, but it's actually undead, so use fire and healing abilities, kupo!
tip_battle.title: Phantom Train

dungeons.epilogue: The heroes have discovered that the train they boarded is none other than the Phantom Train, a ghostly locomotive that carries the souls of the departed to the other side. The only way to get off the train was to stop the engine, so they fought their way through to the engine room--only to be attacked by the train itself! Prevailing, the heroes gladly disembarked and continued on their way to Narshe.
dungeons.name: Phantom Train
dungeons.prologue: Sabin, Shadow, and Cyan have escaped the Imperial Camp and wandered into a forest, where they discover a mysterious train. No sooner do they board to investigate than the whistle blows and the train lurches into motion!

sp_scores.title: Exploit Orthros's weakness to fire attacks.
Exploit Typhon's weakness to ice attacks.

tip_battle.message: Orthros and Typhon have different vulnerabilities, kupo. Use fire and lightning on Orthros, and water and ice on Typhon! Typhon uses Snort to knock characters out of battle, but going back to the Battle Selection Screen will get them back in the action!
tip_battle.title: Orthros & Typhon

sp_scores.title: Defeat Air Force before it uses Wave Cannon.

tip_battle.message: While Air Force's support Bits are out, it hits with a devastating Wave Cannon attack, kupo! Exploit its vulnerabilities to water and lightning to finish it off before it has the chance to use Wave Cannon, or the battle will be a real washout!
tip_battle.title: Air Force

dungeons.epilogue: The party had made their way to the Floating Continent when Orthros attacked again, this time accompanied by his so-called mentor, Typhon. Even in defeat, Typhon's foul breath blasted the Returners from the deck of the Blackjack. The Empire unleashed Air Force on them as they fell, but they managed to land unharmed on the Floating Continent, where they found Shadow left for dead by the Empire.
dungeons.name: Airship
dungeons.prologue: The party is en route to the Floating Continent by airship in an attempt to put a halt to Gestahl's plans and prevent the end of the world, when they are set upon by Imperial airships.

sp_scores.title: Exploit Crane (Lower)'s weakness to water attacks.
Exploit Crane (Upper)'s weakness to lightning attacks.

tip_battle.message: The Cranes are vulnerable to different elements, kupo, but there's one element that works on both of them: water! Attack with water and you can't go wrong!

dungeons.name: Airship
dungeons.prologue: The party is en route to the Floating Continent by airship in an attempt to put a halt to Gestahl's plans and prevent the end of the world, when they are set upon by Imperial airships.

sp_scores.title: Exploit the Tunnel Armor's weakness to lightning attacks.
Exploit the Tunnel Armor's weakness to water attacks.

tip_battle.message: Tunnel Armor may look like a mechanical brute, but watch out, kupo, lest its magic catches you unawares! Have Magic Break and Shell at the ready, and exploit its weaknesses to lightning and water!
tip_battle.title: Tunnel Armor

dungeons.epilogue: The Magitek Knight Celes has become disenchanted with the very Empire that created her. She turns traitor and is imprisoned until Locke comes to her rescue. With the help of Celes's Runic Blade ability they are able to fight off the Imperial Magitek war machine "Tunnel Armor" and make their way to join the others in the Narshe Mines.
dungeons.name: South Figaro Cave
dungeons.prologue: Locke has come to South Figaro to disrupt the Empire's occupation. Trapped under watchful Imperial eyes, he finds an unlikely ally in Celes, an Imperial general. Together they escape through the cave beneath the town.

sp_scores.title: Exploit the Storm Dragon's weakness to lightning attacks.
Win without Cyan being KO'd.

tip_battle.message: The Storm Dragon uses abilities that hit the entire party, like Cyclonic! Use Regen and Life's Touch to keep your party healing throughout the battle, kupo!
tip_battle.title: Storm Dragon

dungeons.epilogue: As expected, Cyan was on Mt. Zozo. He had been sending Lola letters, pretending to be her deceased boyfriend. The sight of his old friends convinced him he could not stand by and watch the world fall apart, and so Cyan joined Celes's party.
dungeons.name: Mt. Zozo
dungeons.prologue: The party follows one of Cyan's carrier pigeons to Maranda, where they find a letter they suspect is from Cyan. They send a reply and follow the pigeon as it wings its way toward Mt. Zozo.

sp_scores.title: Exploit Orthros's weakness to fire attacks.
Exploit Orthros's weakness to lightning attacks.

tip_battle.message: When you face off against Orthros in the Passage of the Eidolons, he has some new tricks up his tentacles, kupo--abilities that hit the whole party! Use abilities like Magic Break and Shell to lessen the damage!
tip_battle.title: Orthros

dungeons.epilogue: The party succeeded in finding the espers after yet another encounter with Orthros, and had just persuaded them to forge a truce with the Empire, when Kefka arrived and began transforming the espers into Magicite. The peace treaty had merely been a ploy to draw the espers out of hiding. Meanwhile, Gestahl discovered the statues of the Warring Triad on the Floating Continent and began to lift it into the sky.
dungeons.name: Esper Caves
dungeons.prologue: The party makes their way to the Esper Caves in an attempt to persuade the espers to reconcile with the Empire. Meanwhile, Emperor Gestahl advances through the Cave to the Sealed Gate...

sp_scores.title: Exploit the Magitek Armor's weakness to lightning attacks.

tip_battle.message: Short-circuit Magitek Armor with lightning attacks before it pummels you with Magitek Laser and Metal Kick, kupo!
tip_battle.title: Magitek Armor

dungeons.epilogue: Though an enemy of the resistance, General Leo is considered a man of honor. The same cannot be said of Kefka, who poisons Doma Castle's water supply in the general's absence. Cyan loses his king, wife, and son to the poison while defending the castle. Burning with rage, he launches a suicidal attack on the Imperial Army, but is saved by Sabin. Together they escape the Imperial Camp and make their way to Narshe through the forest to the south.
dungeons.name: Imperial Camp
dungeons.prologue: Separated from the others after a dive into raging waters, Sabin heads for the mines to rejoin the party. On his way, he witnesses an Imperial attack on Doma Castle, and decides to investigate the Imperial Camp.

sp_scores.title: Exploit Orthros's weakness to fire attacks.
Exploit Orthros's weakness to lightning attacks.

tip_battle.message: When you face off against Orthros in the Passage of the Eidolons, he has some new tricks up his tentacles, kupo--abilities that hit the whole party! Use abilities like Magic Break and Shell to lessen the damage!
tip_battle.title: Orthros

dungeons.epilogue: The party succeeded in finding the espers after yet another encounter with Orthros, and had just persuaded them to forge a truce with the Empire, when Kefka arrived and began transforming the espers into Magicite. The peace treaty had merely been a ploy to draw the espers out of hiding. Meanwhile, Gestahl discovered the statues of the Warring Triad on the Floating Continent and began to lift it into the sky.
dungeons.name: Esper Caves
dungeons.prologue: The party makes their way to the Esper Caves in an attempt to persuade the espers to reconcile with the Empire. Meanwhile, Emperor Gestahl advances through the Cave to the Sealed Gate...

sp_scores.title: Exploit the Angler Whelk's weakness to fire attacks.
Defeat the Angler Whelk before it can use Gigavolt.

tip_battle.message: If you attack the Angler Whelk while it's in its shell, it will counter with its Megavolt ability! Not good, kupo! Better aim for the head!
tip_battle.title: Angler Whelk

sp_scores.title: Exploit Dullahan's weakness to fire attacks.

tip_battle.message: Dullahan is vulnerable to fire, kupo, so bring characters with fire abilities to the fight!
tip_battle.title: Dullahan

dungeons.epilogue: Setzer once dreamed of owning the fastest airship in the world, an ambition he shared with his close friend and rival, Darill. After Darill was lost on a test flight of her ship, the Falcon, Setzer restored the wreckage of the Falcon and buried it beneath Darill's tomb. Now the Falcon flies again, carrying the hopes of the Returners with it.
dungeons.name: Darill's Tomb
dungeons.prologue: The airship lost, Setzer despairs. It is Celes who rouses him again, and takes the party to Darill's tomb to find new hope, and new transportation.

sp_scores.title: Exploit the Magitek Armor's weakness to lightning attacks.

tip_battle.message: Short-circuit Magitek Armor with lightning attacks before it pummels you with Magitek Laser and Metal Kick, kupo!
tip_battle.title: Magitek Armor

dungeons.epilogue: Kefka sets fire to Figaro Castle and demands that Terra be handed over to him. Edgar rejects Kefka's demands and flees with Locke and Terra on chocobos, giving the signal that triggers the castle's self-defense mechanism, submerging it safely in the sand. Fending off Kefka's soldiers, the heroes make their way back to the Returner Hideout.
dungeons.name: Figaro Castle
dungeons.prologue: Locke and Terra have escaped the mines to the desert castle of Figaro, but the arm of the Empire reaches after them with Kefka's approach.

sp_scores.title: Defeat Nelapa without being KO'd.

tip_battle.message: Nelapa uses Doom at the beginning of the battle. Luckily it doesn't have much HP, so come out swinging with ice and lightning attacks, kupo!
tip_battle.title: Nelapa

dungeons.epilogue: The Returners made it to the Blackjack, dispatching Kefka's underling Nelapa along the way, only to find that Shadow had yet to return. They waited as the Floating Continent disintegrated around them, and just when it seemed all was lost, Shadow finally arrived. Jumping for their lives, they landed on the Blackjack before it too was torn apart, scattering the Returners far and wide.
dungeons.name: Floating Continent 2
dungeons.prologue: With the seal broken, the power of the Warring Triad is unleashed, and the party is forced to flee the crumbling Floating Continent. While Shadow deals with Kefka, the party hurries to the airship.

sp_scores.title: Exploit Flame Eater's weakness to ice attacks.

tip_battle.message: Flame Eater is vulnerable to ice, kupo! Just watch out for the balloons and grenades it summons with Bomblet--when they Self-Destruct, it really hurts!
tip_battle.title: Flame Eater

dungeons.epilogue: In search of the espers, the Returners consulted with the monster expert Strago in the remote village of Thamasa, only to be given the cold shoulder. While the party spent the night in the village, a blaze engulfed Strago's house, with a young village girl named Relm trapped inside. As thanks for extinguishing the Flame Eater responsible, Strago agreed to guide them to the Esper Caves.
dungeons.name: Thamasa
dungeons.prologue: Terra's magic opens the Sealed Gate to the Esper World, and the espers spill out, driving away the Imperial forces. Fearing the espers, the Empire sues for peace, and asks for the Returners' help in tracking down the scattered espers before they cause more damage.

tip_battle.message: The Guard Leader appears with 2 Silver Lobos at his side. Focus your attacks on one target to thin their numbers. Use target to your advantage!
tip_battle.title: Guard Leader

dungeons.epilogue: The treasure hunter Locke rushes into the mines to save Terra, who he finds unconscious. Imperial guards attack, and Locke is only able to escape with Terra thanks to the aid of a band of moogles. Safe for the time being, Locke takes Terra to Figaro Castle to meet with fellow Returner Edgar.
dungeons.name: Abandoned Mineshaft
dungeons.prologue: Freed from the Empire's hold on her mind, Terra flees Imperial guards and seeks refuge in the mines.

sp_scores.title: Exploit Ipooh's weakness to fire attacks.
Defeat Vargas without being KO'd.

tip_battle.message: If you don't bring down the 2 Ipoohs that appear with Vargas, you won't be able to hurt him, kupo! Exploit the Ipoohs' weakness to fire to take them down first!
tip_battle.title: Vargas

dungeons.epilogue: Terra and her allies are attacked on the summit of Mt. Kolts by the martial artist Vargas. Things are looking bad for the party until Sabin appears and takes on their assailant. It is revealed that Sabin was a disciple of Vargas's father, Duncan. He had been in pursuit of Vargas to avenge Duncan's death at the hands of his own son. Sabin prevails and accompanies the party back to the Returner Hideout.
dungeons.name: Mt. Kolts
dungeons.prologue: Fleeing their pursuers at Figaro Castle, Terra and the others make for the Returner Hideout, but on the way they must pass over Mt. Kolts where a mysterious figure awaits them...

sp_scores.title: Exploit Ifrit's weakness to ice attacks.
Exploit Shiva's weakness to fire attacks.

tip_battle.message: Ifrit and Shiva appear on alternating turns, and they're vulnerable to opposite elements. Time your attacks carefully, kupo! Use ice on Ifrit and fire on Shiva, or you'll end up healing the enemy!
tip_battle.title: Ifrit & Shiva

dungeons.epilogue: Locke's team recovered the magicite of Ifrit and Shiva, who had been discarded by Kefka after he drained their powers. The party then proceeded further into the Magitek Research Facility, freeing espers as they went, when Kefka made another appearance, insinuating that Celes was an Imperial spy. To prove her loyalty Celes teleported Kefka, his guards, and herself away, giving her friends a chance to escape.
dungeons.name: Magitek Factory
dungeons.prologue: The party has infiltrated the Imperial capital of Vector in hopes of waking Terra. Aided by their fellow Returners, they enter the Magitek Factory where the espers are being held.

sp_scores.title: Exploit Humbaba's weakness to poison attacks.

tip_battle.message: Can you guess how much damage Humbaba's 1000 Needles attack does? A thousand, kupo! It's not a trick question. He's vulnerable to poison damage, so bring spells like Bio to this fight!
tip_battle.title: Humbaba

dungeons.epilogue: In Tzen, Celes rushed to aid Sabin as he held up a collapsing building to save a child trapped inside. Reunited once more, the allies vowed to gather their lost friends and end Kefka's reign of terror. Together they traveled to Mobliz, only to find Terra in a losing battle against Humbaba, a demon who had set his sights on the orphaned children Terra had been caring for.
dungeons.name: Mobliz
dungeons.prologue: Celes washes ashore near Albrook and learns from the townsfolk that Sabin is in Tzen, and Terra is in Mobliz.

sp_scores.title: Defeat Ultima Weapon without being KO'd.

tip_battle.message: Ultima Weapon packs powerful magic attacks, kupo, and it doesn't have any special vulnerabilities. Weaken it with abilities like Armor Break, Power Break, and Magic Break!
tip_battle.title: Ultima Weapon

dungeons.epilogue: Forging their way past Ultima Weapon, the Returners reached the center of the Floating Continent where they found the statues of the Warring Triad. Gestahl turned their power against the party, temporarily paralyzing all but Celes. Kefka then offered to overlook her betrayal if she would kill her companions, but she refused and attacked. Wounded, Kefka flew into a rage and broke the seal on the Warring Triad, killing Gestahl when he tried to intervene.
dungeons.name: Floating Continent 1
dungeons.prologue: The party now makes for the center of the Floating Continent in order to keep Gestahl and Kefka from claiming the statues of the Warring Triad, said to contain the power to destroy the world.

sp_scores.title: Exploit the Storm Dragon's weakness to lightning attacks.

tip_battle.message: The Storm Dragon uses abilities that hit the entire party, like Cyclonic! Use Regen and Life's Touch to keep your party healing throughout the battle, kupo!
tip_battle.title: Storm Dragon

dungeons.epilogue: As expected, Cyan was on Mt. Zozo. He had been sending Lola letters, pretending to be her deceased boyfriend. The sight of his old friends convinced him he could not stand by and watch the world fall apart, and so Cyan joined Celes's party.
dungeons.name: Mt. Zozo
dungeons.prologue: The party follows one of Cyan's carrier pigeons to Maranda, where they find a letter they suspect is from Cyan. They send a reply and follow the pigeon as it wings its way toward Mt. Zozo.

sp_scores.title: Exploit Ipooh's weakness to fire attacks.
Defeat Vargas without being KO'd.

tip_battle.message: If you don't bring down the 2 Ipoohs that appear with Vargas, you won't be able to hurt him, kupo! Exploit the Ipoohs' weakness to fire to take them down first!
tip_battle.title: Vargas

dungeons.epilogue: Terra and her allies are attacked on summit of Mt. Kolts by the martial artist Vargas. Things are looking bad for the party until Sabin appears and takes on their assailant. It is revealed that Sabin and his twin brother, Edgar, were disciples of Vargas's father who now seek to avenge their master's death at the hands of his own son. Sabin prevails and accompanies the party back to the Returner Hideout.
dungeons.name: Mt. Kolts
dungeons.prologue: Fleeing their pursuers at Figaro Castle, Terra and the others make for the Returner Hideout, but on the way they must pass over Mt. Kolts where a mysterious figure awaits them...

sp_scores.title: Exploit the Behemoth King's weakness to poison attacks.
Exploit the Undead Behemoth King's weakness to holy attacks.

tip_battle.message: The Behemoth King wields powerful magic, kupo! He's vulnerable to fire and poison attacks, and he's not resistant to instant KO, so you can even try using Death on him! When he returns in his undead form, use fire and holy attacks. The Undead Behemoth King isn't resistant to instant KO, but you'll need to use Raise on it instead--it's undead, kupo!
tip_battle.title: Behemoth King & Undead Behemoth King

dungeons.epilogue: Interceptor led the party into the depths of the cave, where they discovered Shadow lying on the cold stone. They took him to Thamasa to receive care, but shortly after, Shadow disappeared…
dungeons.name: Cave on the Veldt
dungeons.prologue: The party joins Gau, and together they head for the Cave on the Veldt where they find Shadow's trusty hound, Interceptor.

sp_scores.title: Exploit the Behemoth King's weakness to poison attacks.
Exploit the Undead Behemoth King's weakness to holy attacks.

tip_battle.message: The Behemoth King wields powerful magic, kupo! He's vulnerable to fire and poison attacks, and he's not resistant to instant KO, so you can even try using Death on him! When he returns in his undead form, use fire and holy attacks. The Undead Behemoth King isn't resistant to instant KO, but you'll need to use Raise on it instead--it's undead, kupo!
tip_battle.title: Behemoth King & Undead Behemoth King

dungeons.epilogue: Interceptor led the party into the depths of the cave, where they discovered Shadow lying on the cold stone. They took him to Thamasa to receive care, but shortly after, Shadow disappeared…
dungeons.name: Cave on the Veldt
dungeons.prologue: The party joins Gau, and together they head for the Cave on the Veldt where they find Shadow's trusty hound, Interceptor.

sp_scores.title: Exploit the Black Dragon's weakness to fire attacks.

tip_battle.message: The Black Dragon is undead, kupo! Use fire and healing spells to make it just ordinary dead!
tip_battle.title: Black Dragon

dungeons.epilogue: On the island, Celes did all she could to tend to Cid's illness. She saw him as her grandfather, for it was Cid who raised her as a Magitek knight. Restored to health, Cid gave her a raft, and Celes voyaged off into the ocean alone, hoping beyond hope that her friends were still alive.
dungeons.name: Solitary Island
dungeons.prologue: Celes wakes in a small hut on an unknown island to find that Cid has been taking care of her for an entire year. Now Cid has fallen sick and she must return the favor.

sp_scores.title: Exploit Dadaluma's weakness to poison attacks.

tip_battle.message: Dadaluma uses powerful abilities and potions to stay healed, but he's vulnerable to poison elemental damage, so spells like Bio come highly recommended, kupo! For some reason the Poison ability won't work on him, so don't use it, kupo!
tip_battle.title: Dadaluma

dungeons.epilogue: The party continued their search for Terra, despite difficulties in Zozo and run-ins with street thugs. After administering a beating to the head hoodlum, Dadaluma, they discovered Terra unconscious, but alive. The esper Ramuh, who was caring for Terra, informed the group that the espers held by the Empire may be able to awaken her. Transforming himself into Magicite, he entrusted his power to the Returners.
dungeons.name: Zozo
dungeons.prologue: Following word that Terra has been seen, the party goes from village to village looking for her. They eventually reach the town of Zozo, an impoverished hotbed of scum and villainy.

sp_scores.title: Exploit the Magitek Armor's weakness to lightning attacks.

tip_battle.message: Short-circuit Magitek Armor with lightning attacks before it pummels you with Magitek Laser and Metal Kick, kupo!
tip_battle.title: Magitek Armor

dungeons.epilogue: Kefka sets fire to Figaro Castle and demands that Terra be handed over to him. Edgar rejects Kefka's demands and flees with Locke and Terra on chocobos, giving the signal that triggers the castle's self-defense mechanism, submerging it safely in the sand. Fending off Kefka's soldiers, the heroes make their way back to the Returner Hideout.
dungeons.name: Figaro Castle
dungeons.prologue: Locke and Terra have escaped the mines to the desert castle of Figaro, but the arm of the Empire reaches after them with Kefka's approach.

sp_scores.title: Exploit the Magitek Armor's weakness to lightning attacks.

tip_battle.message: Short-circuit Magitek Armor with lightning attacks before it pummels you with Magitek Laser and Metal Kick, kupo!
tip_battle.title: Magitek Armor

dungeons.epilogue: Though an enemy of the resistance, General Leo is considered a man of honor. The same cannot be said of Kefka, who poisons Doma Castle's water supply in the general's absence. Cyan loses his king, wife, and son to the poison while defending the castle. Burning with rage, he launches a suicidal attack on the Imperial Army, but is saved by Sabin. Together they escape the Imperial Camp and make their way to Narshe through the forest to the south.
dungeons.name: Imperial Camp
dungeons.prologue: Separated from the others after a dive into raging waters, Sabin heads for the mines to rejoin the party. On his way, he witnesses an Imperial attack on Doma Castle, and decides to investigate the Imperial Camp.

sp_scores.title: Exploit Tentacle (Bottom-Right)'s weakness to ice attacks.
Exploit Tentacle (Bottom-Left)'s weakness to fire attacks.

tip_battle.message: Each of the four Tentacles has a different vulnerability, kupo. Use the right element on the right tentacle, or you'll end up healing them!
tip_battle.title: Tentacles

dungeons.epilogue: Celes and Sabin followed Gerad into Figaro Castle, which had lost its ability to move through the desert sands. When they reached the engine room, they discovered why: a bizarre tentacle-like creature had wrapped itself around the castle's engine. Edgar finally abandoned his somewhat unconvincing guise as Gerad in the ensuing battle, and with the creature defeated, the castle was able to surface at last.
dungeons.name: Figaro Castle 2
dungeons.prologue: Celes' party leaves Terra in Mobliz and continues on to the port town of Nikeah, where they encounter a bandit named Gerad trying to enter Figaro Castle. The bandit looks suspiciously similar to Edgar...

sp_scores.title: Exploit Deathgaze's weakness to fire attacks.
Exploit Deathgaze's weakness to holy attacks.

tip_battle.message: Deathgaze uses Death to KO characters one by one, so bring Revive and Raise to get everyone back on their feet! It's vulnerable to fire and holy attacks, so hit hard and fast with those!
tip_battle.title: Deathgaze

dungeons.epilogue: Setzer and his friends had taken to the skies aboard the late Darill's airship, the Falcon. Yet no sooner did they start on their journey than they were attacked by Deathgaze. Chasing down the fleeing monster, they vanquished it, and once again set out across the skies.
dungeons.name: Falcon
dungeons.prologue: Setzer puts his grief behind him as he boards the restored Falcon and sets off on a journey with his old friends to see the ruined world.

sp_scores.title: Exploit Ifrit's weakness to ice attacks.
Exploit Shiva's weakness to fire attacks.

tip_battle.message: Ifrit and Shiva appear on alternating turns, and they're vulnerable to opposite elements. Time your attacks carefully, kupo! Use ice on Ifrit and fire on Shiva, or you'll end up healing the enemy!
tip_battle.title: Ifrit & Shiva

dungeons.epilogue: Locke's team recovered the magicite of Ifrit and Shiva, who had been discarded by Kefka after he drained their powers. The party then proceeded further into the Magitek Research Facility, freeing espers as they went, when Kefka made another appearance, insinuating that Celes was an Imperial spy. To prove her loyalty Celes teleported Kefka, his guards, and herself away, giving her friends a chance to escape.
dungeons.name: Magitek Factory
dungeons.prologue: The party has infiltrated the Imperial capital of Vector in hopes of waking Terra. Aided by their fellow Returners, they enter the Magitek Factory where the espers are being held.

sp_scores.title: Exploit the Black Dragon's weakness to fire attacks.

tip_battle.message: The Black Dragon is undead, kupo! Use fire and healing spells to make it just ordinary dead!
tip_battle.title: Black Dragon

dungeons.epilogue: On the island, Celes did all she could to tend to Cid's illness. She saw him as her grandfather, for it was Cid who raised her as a Magitek knight. Restored to health, Cid gave her a raft, and Celes voyaged off into the ocean alone, hoping beyond hope that her friends were still alive.
dungeons.name: Solitary Island
dungeons.prologue: Celes wakes in a small hut on an unknown island to find that Cid has been taking care of her for an entire year. Now Cid has fallen sick and she must return the favor.

sp_scores.title: Exploit Orthros's weakness to fire attacks.

tip_battle.message: Orthros moves around the opera house like he owns the place, kupo! His actions change depending on where he is, but not his vulnerabilities. Fire and lightning will work throughout the battle!
tip_battle.title: Orthros

dungeons.epilogue: Setzer left a letter revealing his intention to kidnap the opera singer Maria during a performance, so Locke devised a plot to use Celes, a dead ringer for Maria, as bait to lure him out. Orthros appeared once more in an attempt to ruin their plans, to no avail. The group made contact with Setzer, and after much persuasion he offered his assistance.
dungeons.name: Opera House
dungeons.prologue: The party heads to the Opera House in order to make contact with Setzer, who owns an airship that can get them across the sea to the Empire.

sp_scores.title: Exploit the Angler Whelk's weakness to fire attacks.
Defeat the Angler Whelk before it can use Gigavolt.

tip_battle.message: If you attack the Angler Whelk while it's in its shell, it will counter with its Megavolt ability! Not good, kupo! Better aim for the head!
tip_battle.title: Angler Whelk

sp_scores.title: Exploit Dullahan's weakness to fire attacks.

tip_battle.message: Dullahan is vulnerable to fire, kupo, so bring characters with fire abilities to the fight!
tip_battle.title: Dullahan

dungeons.epilogue: Setzer once dreamed of owning the fastest airship in the world, an ambition he shared with his close friend and rival, Darill. After Darill was lost on a test flight of her ship, the Falcon, Setzer restored the wreckage of the Falcon and buried it beneath Darill's tomb. Now the Falcon flies again, carrying the hopes of the Returners with it.
dungeons.name: Darill's Tomb
dungeons.prologue: The airship lost, Setzer despairs. It is Celes who rouses him again, and takes the party to Darill's tomb to find new hope, and new transportation.

sp_scores.title: Defeat Nelapa without being KO'd.

tip_battle.message: Nelapa uses Doom at the beginning of the battle. Luckily it doesn't have much HP, so come out swinging with ice and lightning attacks, kupo!
tip_battle.title: Nelapa

dungeons.epilogue: The Returners made it to the Blackjack, dispatching Kefka's underling Nelapa along the way, only to find that Shadow had yet to return. They waited as the Floating Continent disintegrated around them, and just when it seemed all was lost, Shadow finally arrived. Jumping for their lives, they landed on the Blackjack before it too was torn apart, scattering the Returners far and wide.
dungeons.name: Floating Continent 2
dungeons.prologue: With the seal broken, the power of the Warring Triad is unleashed, and the party is forced to flee the crumbling Floating Continent. While Shadow deals with Kefka, the party hurries to the airship.
